# BYOA agent setup

BYOA runs an app user's Codex app-server in the developer's Cloudflare account. The user signs in with ChatGPT. The developer does not provide one shared OpenAI API key.

## install

```bash
npx byoa deploy
npm install byoa
```

No clone is required for an app integration. Repository contributors should read `AGENTS.md`, `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/deploy.md`, `docs/demo.md`, and `docs/security.md` before changing BYOA itself.

## deploy the runner

Requirements: Cloudflare Workers Paid, Containers, and an authenticated Wrangler session. R2 is required before enabling durable credential and workspace persistence.

The deploy command creates `BYOA_APP_SECRET` when one is not provided. Save it in the developer backend, which exchanges it for short-lived browser session tokens. Never put it or a Cloudflare credential in browser code.

## add the client

Use `byoa` for the protocol client, `byoa/server` in the trusted backend, and `byoa/react` only if the app uses React. The package is publish-ready but still needs its first npm publish.

BYOA is an agent runtime, not a chat abstraction. Use `agent.threads`, `agent.turns`, `agent.workspace`, `agent.models`, `agent.mcp`, and `agent.extensions`. Keep the raw `request()` and event stream available for the rest of Codex app-server.

Files belong under `/workspace`. Use thread `developerInstructions` for app behavior, `AGENTS.md` and skills for durable repo behavior, hooks for lifecycle enforcement, and `outputSchema` for machine-readable output.

Dynamic tools require `experimentalApi: true`. Use `agent.onToolCall()` only for browser-safe tools. Put privileged tools behind the app backend or authenticated MCP; the signed backend tool router is not finished.

The example text and image integration lives in `apps/demo` and is deployed at `https://byoa-demo.pages.dev`. It reads image-generation capability from the signed-in account and renders final `imageGeneration` items.

## do not improvise around blockers

If Containers are unavailable, stop and enable them. The current alpha runner is ephemeral; do not imply durable sessions until R2 persistence lands. Do not replace tenant isolation with a shared process or store agent credentials in the workspace.
